verses.text_plain: The word of the Lord that came to Joel the son of Pethuel.
verses.verse_html: 1The word of the Lord that came to Joel the son of Pethuel.

verses.text_plain: Hear this, ye old men, and give ear, all ye inhabitants of the land. Hath this been in your days, or even in the days of your fathers?
verses.verse_html: 2Hear this, ye old men, and give ear, all ye inhabitants of the land. Hath this been in your days, or even in the days of your fathers?

tokens.text: Hath this been in your days

verses.text_plain: Tell ye your children of it, and let your children tell their children, and their children another generation.
verses.verse_html: 3Tell ye your children of it, and let your children tell their children, and their children another generation.

verses.text_plain: That which the palmerworm hath left hath the locust eaten; and that which the locust hath left hath the cankerworm eaten; and that which the cankerworm hath left hath the caterpiller eaten.
verses.verse_html:
4That which the palmerworm hath left hath the locust eaten; and that which the locust hath left hath the cankerworm eaten; and that which the cankerworm hath left hath the caterpiller eaten. ▼
▼ That which the palmerworm…: Heb. The residue of the palmerworm

footnotes.body_text: ▼ That which the palmerworm…: Heb. The residue of the palmerworm
footnotes.body_html: ▼ That which the palmerworm…: Heb. The residue of the palmerworm

verses.text_plain: Awake, ye drunkards, and weep; and howl, all ye drinkers of wine, because of the new wine; for it is cut off from your mouth.
verses.verse_html: 5Awake, ye drunkards, and weep; and howl, all ye drinkers of wine, because of the new wine; for it is cut off from your mouth.

verses.text_plain: For a nation is come up upon my land, strong, and without number, whose teeth are the teeth of a lion, and he hath the cheek teeth of a great lion.
verses.verse_html: 6For a nation is come up upon my land, strong, and without number, whose teeth are the teeth of a lion, and he hath the cheek teeth of a great lion.

tokens.text: and he hath the cheek teeth

verses.text_plain: He hath laid my vine waste, and barked my fig tree: he hath made it clean bare, and cast it away; the branches thereof are made white.
verses.verse_html:
7He hath laid my vine waste, and barked my fig tree: he hath made it clean bare, and cast it away; the branches thereof are made white. ▼
▼ barked…: Heb. laid my fig tree for a barking

footnotes.body_text: ▼ barked…: Heb. laid my fig tree for a barking
footnotes.body_html: ▼ barked…: Heb. laid my fig tree for a barking

verses.text_plain: Lament like a virgin girded with sackcloth for the husband of her youth.
verses.verse_html: 8Lament like a virgin girded with sackcloth for the husband of her youth.

verses.text_plain: The meat offering and the drink offering is cut off from the house of the Lord; the priests, the Lord’s ministers, mourn.
verses.verse_html: 9The meat offering and the drink offering is cut off from the house of the Lord; the priests, the Lord’s ministers, mourn.

verses.text_plain: The field is wasted, the land mourneth; for the corn is wasted: the new wine is dried up, the oil languisheth.
verses.verse_html: 10The field is wasted, the land mourneth; for the corn is wasted: the new wine is dried up, the oil languisheth.

verses.text_plain: Be ye ashamed, O ye husbandmen; howl, O ye vinedressers, for the wheat and for the barley; because the harvest of the field is perished.
verses.verse_html: 11Be ye ashamed, O ye husbandmen; howl, O ye vinedressers, for the wheat and for the barley; because the harvest of the field is perished.

verses.text_plain: The vine is dried up, and the fig tree languisheth; the pomegranate tree, the palm tree also, and the apple tree, even all the trees of the field, are withered: because joy is withered away from the sons of men.
verses.verse_html: 12The vine is dried up, and the fig tree languisheth; the pomegranate tree, the palm tree also, and the apple tree, even all the trees of the field, are withered: because joy is withered away from the sons of men.

verses.text_plain: Gird yourselves, and lament, ye priests: howl, ye ministers of the altar: come, lie all night in sackcloth, ye ministers of my God: for the meat offering and the drink offering is withholden from the house of your God.
verses.verse_html: 13Gird yourselves, and lament, ye priests: howl, ye ministers of the altar: come, lie all night in sackcloth, ye ministers of my God: for the meat offering and the drink offering is withholden from the house of your God.

verses.text_plain: Sanctify ye a fast, call a solemn assembly, gather the elders and all the inhabitants of the land into the house of the Lord your God, and cry unto the Lord,
verses.verse_html:
14Sanctify ye a fast, call a solemn assembly, gather the elders and all the inhabitants of the land into the house of the Lord your God, and cry unto the Lord, ▼
▼ solemn…: or, day of restraint

footnotes.body_html: ▼ solemn…: or, day of restraint

verses.text_plain: Alas for the day! for the day of the Lord is at hand, and as a destruction from the Almighty shall it come.
verses.verse_html: 15Alas for the day! for the day of the Lord is at hand, and as a destruction from the Almighty shall it come.

verses.text_plain: Is not the meat cut off before our eyes, yea, joy and gladness from the house of our God?
verses.verse_html: 16Is not the meat cut off before our eyes, yea, joy and gladness from the house of our God?

verses.text_plain: The seed is rotten under their clods, the garners are laid desolate, the barns are broken down; for the corn is withered.
verses.verse_html:
17The seed is rotten under their clods, the garners are laid desolate, the barns are broken down; for the corn is withered. ▼
▼ seed: Heb. grains

verses.text_plain: How do the beasts groan! the herds of cattle are perplexed, because they have no pasture; yea, the flocks of sheep are made desolate.
verses.verse_html: 18How do the beasts groan! the herds of cattle are perplexed, because they have no pasture; yea, the flocks of sheep are made desolate.

verses.text_plain: O Lord, to thee will I cry: for the fire hath devoured the pastures of the wilderness, and the flame hath burned all the trees of the field.
verses.verse_html:
19O Lord, to thee will I cry: for the fire hath devoured the pastures of the wilderness, and the flame hath burned all the trees of the field. ▼
▼ pastures: or, habitations

verses.text_plain: The beasts of the field cry also unto thee: for the rivers of waters are dried up, and the fire hath devoured the pastures of the wilderness.
verses.verse_html: 20The beasts of the field cry also unto thee: for the rivers of waters are dried up, and the fire hath devoured the pastures of the wilderness.

tokens.text: also unto thee: for the rivers
